Greetings,

Peter

Pascal Thubert (pthubert) schreef op 2014-07-10 15:10:
> Certainly Peter;
> 
> Though I'd be glad to invite others with a different twist to help.
> 
> I'll note that most of the changes I'm suggesting are not specific to
> RPL, and the problem is not limited to RPL either.
> 
> A critical info for RPL is the TID that must be set by the client, and
> most DV protocols in the MANET space will have a similar sequence
> number so as to support movement and eliminate stale routes.
> 
> The RPL instance ID is an option, that may be omitted if the routing
> protocol does not support multiple instances.
> 
> Though my original intention was a one shot draft, maybe it would make
> sense for the group to make it more general and then publish in order
> to justify a 6775bis.
> 
> What do you think?
> 
> Pascal
> 
> 
