Certainly Peter;=20

Though I'd be glad to invite others with a different twist to help. =20

I'll note that most of the changes I'm suggesting are not specific to RPL, =
and the problem is not limited to RPL either.

A critical info for RPL is the TID that must be set by the client, and most=
 DV protocols in the MANET space will have a similar sequence number so as =
to support movement and eliminate stale routes.=20

The RPL instance ID is an option, that may be omitted if the routing protoc=
ol does not support multiple instances.=20

Though my original intention was a one shot draft, maybe it would make sens=
e for the group to make it more general and then publish in order to justif=
y a 6775bis.

What do you think?

Pascal


