Hi Carsten,

Perhaps my usage of "RPL" wording is not a correct choice of word.
Though RFC6775 is primarily a host-router protocol,   it can interact with =
a routing protocol while bootstrapping [ section 10.3].

If we expand our host-router views a little bit and look at movement(join,l=
eave etc.) between two IOT networks (real deployments) then TID bit is nece=
ssary in the ND - as we realize after working on the efficient-nd.

Also, I believe RPL network uses ND for address autoconfiguration at the st=
artup to separate the addressing and routing behavior and thus it depends o=
n 6lowpan-nd.

Regards,
-Samita



