Note that RFC 6282 already provides the option:
- If the IID can be derived from MAC address, great.
- If not, things will still work just with reduced efficiency.

Section 10 of RFC 4944 also provides the same option, but has since been re=
placed by the encoding specified in RFC 6282.

Also note that 802.15.4 interfaces have both a stable MAC address (EUI-64) =
and a locally-significant, dynamic MAC address (Short Address).  Many of th=
e arguments against MAC-address-based IIDs may not apply when using Short A=
ddresses.

